---
title: Styled Range Slider
description: A custom-styled range input using CSS track and thumb pseudo-elements.
slug: range-slider
cssFile: range-slider.css
explanation: <code>appearance:none</code> removes the browser default. The track is styled directly on the <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> element. The thumb is styled via the vendor-specific <code>::-webkit-slider-thumb</code> and <code>::-moz-range-thumb</code> pseudo-elements. Both Webkit and Firefox need separate rules since they don't share a standard pseudo-element name yet.
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;align-items:center">
	<input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="40">
	<input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="70">
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="50">
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
input[type="range"] {
  appearance: none;
  width: 220px;
  height: 6px;
  background: #2a2a2d;
  border-radius: 999px;
  outline: none;
  cursor: pointer;
}

input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
  appearance: none;
  width: 22px;
  height: 22px;
  background: #5b4cdb;
  border-radius: 50%;
  box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(91,76,219,.4);
}

input[type="range"]::-moz-range-thumb {
  width: 22px;
  height: 22px;
  background: #5b4cdb;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 50%;
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
